# ThoughtID Rules — Add to your project CLAUDE.md

@thoughtid
  no-assume-provenance: file content does not equal committed code.
  git diff HEAD before claiming already done. Before EVERY response:
  did I assume anything?

  thoughtid-integrity: every factual claim gets a TID via thoughtid.py.
  Evidence must be from command execution, not free text.
  File claims require prove-file (forces diff into context).
  Unverified claims at checkpoint = Error Code 1.
  The Watcher sees all.
